1
00:00:06,656 --> 00:00:11,904
 ♫ I still remember ♫ 

2
00:00:11,904 --> 00:00:15,518
 ♫ Your flickering gaze ♫ 

3
00:00:15,518 --> 00:00:17,303
 ♫ With a sense of excitement ♫ 

4
00:00:17,303 --> 00:00:20,832
 ♫ You vowed eternal love ♫ 

5
00:00:20,832 --> 00:00:25,984
 ♫ But over time, you've forgotten ♫ 

6
00:00:25,984 --> 00:00:31,232
 ♫ Promises drowned in life's twists ♫ 

7
00:00:31,232 --> 00:00:34,720
 ♫ Only memories remain like scattered fireworks ♫ 

8
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:38,184
 ♫ When I turned to walk away ♫ 

9
00:00:38,184 --> 00:00:42,816
 ♫ If I could go back to the day we parted ♫ 

10
00:00:42,816 --> 00:00:49,088
 ♫ I'd never let go of your hand ♫ 

11
00:00:49,088 --> 00:00:53,824
 ♫ I cannot hide my feelings ♫ 

12
00:00:53,824 --> 00:00:55,904
 ♫ I'm about to be out of control ♫ 

13
00:00:55,904 --> 00:01:01,088
 ♫ As breathing turns weightless ♫ 

14
00:01:01,088 --> 00:01:03,104
 ♫ All I possess is drowned ♫ 

15
00:01:03,104 --> 00:01:06,072
 ♫ The me who still loves you deeply ♫ 

16
00:01:06,072 --> 00:01:07,968
 ♫ Has never changed ♫ 

17
00:01:07,968 --> 00:01:11,296
 ♫ If miracles could exist ♫ 

18
00:01:11,296 --> 00:01:13,351
 ♫ Promises would be kept ♫ 

19
00:01:13,351 --> 00:01:15,328
 ♫ Please remember ♫ 

20
00:01:15,328 --> 00:01:20,343
 ♫ The dream where you see me ♫ 

21
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:30,496
 

22
00:01:30,496 --> 00:01:34,016
 

23
00:02:00,390 --> 00:02:05,390
This is the seaside vacation villa
you told me about?

24
00:02:05,390 --> 00:02:09,110
Just an old house in the countryside.
You lied to me.

25
00:02:09,110 --> 00:02:10,784
You're overthinking it. Not here.

26
00:02:10,784 --> 00:02:13,850
You'll stay over there.

27
00:02:22,770 --> 00:02:25,350
Grandma, your grandson is here.

28
00:02:25,350 --> 00:02:29,190
Coming, coming right up.

29
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:33,470
My dear, I've missed you so much.

30
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:36,890
I've cleaned up a room for you. Filled with toys.

31
00:02:36,890 --> 00:02:39,730
Look at this free-range chicken.
It's even got double eyelids.

32
00:02:39,730 --> 00:02:41,550
I'll kill it tonight

33
00:02:41,550 --> 00:02:43,510
and make some nourishing soup for you.

34
00:02:43,510 --> 00:02:47,450
Look how skinny he is, like a little monkey.

35
00:02:49,850 --> 00:02:53,190
It's dirty. I won't eat this.

36
00:02:53,190 --> 00:02:54,390
Still fussy about cleanliness?

37
00:02:54,390 --> 00:02:57,110
You little brat, stop hiding!

38
00:02:57,110 --> 00:02:58,610
Who spoiled you?

39
00:02:58,610 --> 00:03:01,770
Eat it or stay hungry.

40
00:03:02,390 --> 00:03:04,570
Let's go home.

41
00:03:06,010 --> 00:03:08,110
Come, let's go home with me.

42
00:03:09,110 --> 00:03:10,970
Come home with me.

43
00:03:10,970 --> 00:03:13,070
If you don't eat it, we'll save money.

44
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:42,110
When will Mom come take me back?

45
00:03:42,810 --> 00:03:45,110
Do you really dislike this place that much?

46
00:03:46,190 --> 00:03:51,190
But to be fair, I had a harder time
adjusting when I first came.

47
00:03:52,230 --> 00:03:56,410
Really? So you think Grandma's scary, too?

48
00:03:57,190 --> 00:03:59,190
She was much tougher on me than she is on you.

49
00:03:59,190 --> 00:04:01,024
She even beat me before.

50
00:04:02,770 --> 00:04:05,970
But she's all bark and no bite.

51
00:04:05,970 --> 00:04:09,270
Deep down, she cares about us more than anyone.

52
00:04:09,270 --> 00:04:12,690
Right after being discharged from the hospital,
she cleaned your room for you

53
00:04:12,690 --> 00:04:15,350
and even learned your favorite dishes.

54
00:04:15,350 --> 00:04:18,350
She kept asking me when I'd go get you.

55
00:04:20,970 --> 00:04:24,310
But I still miss Mom,

56
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:26,610
even though she made mistakes.

57
00:04:28,730 --> 00:04:30,720
She misses you, too.

58
00:04:32,650 --> 00:04:38,190
But now you have Grandma and me.

59
00:04:38,190 --> 00:04:41,850
Don't worry. We'll all take good care of you.

60
00:04:45,970 --> 00:04:49,910
But it's okay. Take your time.

61
00:04:54,650 --> 00:04:56,430
Ba Dou, Zhuo Feng.

62
00:04:56,430 --> 00:04:59,570
What are you doing? Get back here for dinner!

63
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:02,570
- Coming.
- Hurry up!

64
00:05:03,610 --> 00:05:05,568
Let's go.

65
00:05:24,310 --> 00:05:26,550
How's the little brother adjusting?

66
00:05:26,550 --> 00:05:29,730
Not bad. He's adapting faster than I did.

67
00:05:33,850 --> 00:05:36,450
What're you looking at? Smiling so happily.

68
00:05:37,930 --> 00:05:39,310
Let me show you something.

69
00:05:39,310 --> 00:05:40,690
Look, look quickly!

70
00:05:40,690 --> 00:05:43,650
See? This kitten is so cute.

71
00:05:43,650 --> 00:05:46,190
Let's get a Devon Rex to raise.

72
00:05:46,190 --> 00:05:49,110
They're beautiful and clingy.

73
00:05:49,110 --> 00:05:51,550
Clingy.

74
00:05:51,550 --> 00:05:54,350
The key is that they don't shed much.

75
00:05:55,050 --> 00:05:56,864
No.

76
00:05:58,080 --> 00:06:00,430
Why not?

77
00:06:00,430 --> 00:06:01,930
We already have Ping An.

78
00:06:01,930 --> 00:06:04,550
A cat would make it jealous.

79
00:06:04,550 --> 00:06:07,930
Ping An is barely home anyway.
Why would it be jealous?

80
00:06:07,930 --> 00:06:09,850
If you don't want to raise one, just say so.

81
00:06:09,850 --> 00:06:12,070
Don't use Ping An as an excuse.

82
00:06:13,730 --> 00:06:16,510
Seems you're too devoted to Ping An.

83
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:18,910
No room left for me in your heart.

84
00:06:20,390 --> 00:06:22,610
You're reversing the blame.

85
00:06:22,610 --> 00:06:25,930
You're the one wanting to get a cat
and be unfaithful.

86
00:06:25,930 --> 00:06:27,390
Are you jealous of a cat?

87
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:29,350
I'm already married to you, Li Jin Yu.

88
00:06:29,350 --> 00:06:31,360
I don't care.

89
00:06:33,310 --> 00:06:34,810
Fine, fine.

90
00:06:34,810 --> 00:06:38,430
We'll visit the cattery when we have time.

91
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:41,490
That's more like it. Pinky swear.

92
00:06:43,310 --> 00:06:45,120
Pinky swear.

93
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:47,104
Swear, swear, swear.

94
00:06:49,550 --> 00:06:51,730
Look again.

95
00:06:53,650 --> 00:06:57,650
So adorable, don't you think?

96
00:06:57,650 --> 00:06:59,570
Not as cute as Ping An.

97
00:07:00,430 --> 00:07:01,430
I'm the prettiest.

98
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:03,230
Yes, you're the prettiest.

99
00:07:08,390 --> 00:07:12,310
Finally, wrap it three times around the wrist.

100
00:07:13,770 --> 00:07:16,770
Make sure to wrap it tight.

101
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:19,970
Before we start formal boxing training,

102
00:07:19,970 --> 00:07:21,690
you need to learn to protect your body first.

103
00:07:21,690 --> 00:07:23,310
Keep your wrists inward.

104
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:24,930
- Like this?
- Press them tightly against yourself. Yeah.

105
00:07:24,930 --> 00:07:26,350
- No, this way.
- Like this?

106
00:07:26,350 --> 00:07:28,110
Right, press them against your cheeks.

107
00:07:28,110 --> 00:07:31,850
Then keep your elbows glued to your ribs, right?

108
00:07:31,850 --> 00:07:34,810
- This way?
- To protect your sides from punches.

109
00:07:34,810 --> 00:07:36,470
And these areas, too. Got it?

110
00:07:36,470 --> 00:07:38,528
Let's end today's lesson here, okay?

111
00:07:38,528 --> 00:07:40,288
- Alright.
- Come on.

112
00:07:40,288 --> 00:07:41,472
I'll drive you home.

113
00:07:41,472 --> 00:07:44,190
No, thanks. My mom's picking me up soon.

114
00:07:44,810 --> 00:07:45,970
Is your mom coming?

115
00:07:45,970 --> 00:07:48,030
- Jia Yu.
- Mom!

116
00:07:54,650 --> 00:07:58,150
Here to pick up Jia Yu?

117
00:08:01,470 --> 00:08:04,390
How's business since converting this place
into a restaurant?

118
00:08:04,390 --> 00:08:06,310
It's doing pretty well, huh?

119
00:08:07,550 --> 00:08:10,510
Mostly regular customers.

120
00:08:10,510 --> 00:08:12,570
Not bad.

121
00:08:17,190 --> 00:08:19,550
Let me pack up, and we'll leave.

122
00:08:19,550 --> 00:08:20,850
Okay.

123
00:08:20,850 --> 00:08:21,930
Cheng.

124
00:08:21,930 --> 00:08:25,510
Why weren't you answering?
I finally tracked you down.

125
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:26,550
Liu!

126
00:08:26,550 --> 00:08:28,384
You're here, too?

127
00:08:30,390 --> 00:08:32,970
I scheduled your blind date for tomorrow noon.

128
00:08:32,970 --> 00:08:35,610
Kai, you're going on a blind date?

129
00:08:35,610 --> 00:08:37,390
No, I didn't know about this!

130
00:08:37,390 --> 00:08:38,770
What? What blind date?

131
00:08:38,770 --> 00:08:40,430
Your mom arranged it with me.

132
00:08:40,430 --> 00:08:42,430
Besides, last time at Ya En's shop,

133
00:08:42,430 --> 00:08:44,970
we talked about finding you a girlfriend.

134
00:08:44,970 --> 00:08:47,190
Listen, this girl's got great qualifications.

135
00:08:47,190 --> 00:08:49,600
Meeting her won't hurt. Right?

136
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:50,690
But I--

137
00:08:50,690 --> 00:08:52,770
Ya En, help me convince him.

138
00:08:52,770 --> 00:08:55,550
He's being shy.

139
00:08:55,550 --> 00:08:56,550
My mom--

140
00:08:56,550 --> 00:08:59,550
Exactly! Just meet her.

141
00:08:59,550 --> 00:09:00,730
Don't miss this chance.

142
00:09:00,730 --> 00:09:03,230
Yeah, what's there to be shy about?

143
00:09:03,230 --> 00:09:06,110
Your family already paid the agency fee.

144
00:09:06,110 --> 00:09:09,610
Let me tell you, I'm a professional matchmaker.

145
00:09:09,610 --> 00:09:12,990
Not like those agencies that just take your money.

146
00:09:14,690 --> 00:09:17,810
Right, Liu is reliable.

147
00:09:17,810 --> 00:09:19,310
- Let's go, Jia Yu.
- Mom, let's go.

148
00:09:19,310 --> 00:09:20,960
- We're leaving.
- Okay.

149
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:21,970
Bye, Kai.

150
00:09:21,970 --> 00:09:23,808
You...

151
00:09:25,310 --> 00:09:26,930
But my mom never told me about this.

152
00:09:26,930 --> 00:09:28,512
Your mom already prepaid for the service.

153
00:09:28,512 --> 00:09:29,650
Enough. Listen.

154
00:09:29,650 --> 00:09:31,510
Tomorrow at noon at Tide Restaurant.

155
00:09:31,510 --> 00:09:35,008
Don't be late. Understood?

156
00:09:35,008 --> 00:09:36,890
Don't be late.

157
00:09:36,890 --> 00:09:39,270
Jia Yu, you...

158
00:09:40,510 --> 00:09:42,610
Go, go.

159
00:09:42,610 --> 00:09:44,190
- Don't be late.
- Okay, okay, okay.

160
00:09:44,190 --> 00:09:45,650
- Alright, I'm off.
- Got it.

161
00:09:45,650 --> 00:09:48,010
- Don't be late.
- Okay.

162
00:09:48,010 --> 00:09:50,016
Goodbye, Liu.

163
00:09:51,970 --> 00:09:55,550
Mom, a Ms. Liu told me

164
00:09:55,550 --> 00:09:58,730
you set up a blind date for me tomorrow?

165
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,510
Hello, we have a reservation.

166
00:10:05,510 --> 00:10:07,510
Ms. Fang, right this way.

167
00:10:07,510 --> 00:10:08,850
I thought you hated this restaurant.

168
00:10:08,850 --> 00:10:10,150
Why come here suddenly?

169
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:13,190
People's tastes change as they grow up.

170
00:10:13,190 --> 00:10:15,110
Kai, what a coincidence.

171
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:22,030
Excuse me.

172
00:10:25,050 --> 00:10:28,510
Such a coincidence. Your friend?

173
00:10:28,510 --> 00:10:33,570
My parents wanted me to meet her.

174
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:35,650
Here for a blind date?

175
00:10:35,650 --> 00:10:36,730
No, no.

176
00:10:36,730 --> 00:10:38,110
W-W-Well, enjoy your meal.

177
00:10:38,110 --> 00:10:39,550
We won't third-wheel. Go ahead.

178
00:10:39,550 --> 00:10:42,070
- No.
- Bye, Kai.

179
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:49,390
You order, Jia Yu.

180
00:10:49,390 --> 00:10:50,390
Thank you.

181
00:10:50,390 --> 00:10:53,430
I'll have these fried chicken wings,

182
00:10:53,430 --> 00:10:55,430
a potato salad,

183
00:10:55,430 --> 00:10:59,010
and this... saury?

184
00:10:59,010 --> 00:11:02,810
Sorry about that. I ran into someone I know.

185
00:11:02,810 --> 00:11:08,110
That's okay. Did Liu brief you on me?

186
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:11,430
For drinks, vanilla milk tea.

187
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:13,470
Then an apple cake.

188
00:11:13,470 --> 00:11:15,810
- Here.
- Got it.

189
00:11:23,310 --> 00:11:25,770
The matchmaker who set us up,

190
00:11:25,770 --> 00:11:28,610
didn't she tell you?

191
00:11:28,610 --> 00:11:32,448
Maybe our parents discussed it?

192
00:11:32,448 --> 00:11:35,424
Let me introduce myself.
I'm a kindergarten teacher.

193
00:11:35,424 --> 00:11:37,510
My parents are educators, too.

194
00:11:37,510 --> 00:11:39,510
I'm an only child.

195
00:11:39,510 --> 00:11:41,470
I own both a car and an apartment.

196
00:11:41,470 --> 00:11:45,190
I'm looking for someone compatible in Ningsui.

197
00:11:45,190 --> 00:11:49,970
Chen Jia Yu, did you bring me here on purpose?

198
00:11:49,970 --> 00:11:54,350
Mom, how could you suspect your own son?

199
00:11:54,350 --> 00:11:57,690
Since when does my own son scheme against me?

200
00:11:57,690 --> 00:12:00,910
And when did my mother become so contradictory?

201
00:12:01,550 --> 00:12:03,390
Okay, you win.

202
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:05,550
What do you think of me?

203
00:12:05,550 --> 00:12:07,550
Not bad.

204
00:12:07,550 --> 00:12:09,610
I think we're quite compatible.

205
00:12:09,610 --> 00:12:12,430
Good looks, height,
and financial stability, all satisfactory.

206
00:12:12,430 --> 00:12:15,072
Rare to meet someone with decent features
through blind dates.

207
00:12:15,072 --> 00:12:20,190
Since we both feel good about this,
let's try dating.

208
00:12:26,650 --> 00:12:30,730
Actually, maybe not.

209
00:12:30,730 --> 00:12:33,430
It's not you. It's me.

210
00:12:33,430 --> 00:12:36,550
There's someone I like.

211
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:39,650
She hasn't accepted me yet,

212
00:12:39,650 --> 00:12:41,650
but I won't give up.

213
00:12:41,650 --> 00:12:46,390
I came today to make things clear.

214
00:12:46,390 --> 00:12:48,230
I want to apologize.

215
00:12:48,890 --> 00:12:52,510
That's okay. Having a crush is wonderful.

216
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:55,390
You should've told me earlier
to avoid her misunderstanding.

217
00:12:55,390 --> 00:12:58,470
Let's consider today as making a new friend.

218
00:12:58,470 --> 00:13:00,930
Here's to your success in love.

219
00:13:00,930 --> 00:13:02,510
May you win her heart soon.

220
00:13:02,510 --> 00:13:06,350
Wishing you all the best.
Thank you for understanding.

221
00:13:08,550 --> 00:13:11,770
By the way, I opened a restaurant by the beach.

222
00:13:11,770 --> 00:13:15,190
Bring your girlfriends sometime for a meal.

223
00:13:15,190 --> 00:13:17,230
Absolutely, definitely.

224
00:13:23,650 --> 00:13:25,150
Mom, what are you doing?

225
00:13:25,150 --> 00:13:26,230
Let me take some photos of you.

226
00:13:26,230 --> 00:13:27,850
This place has a nice ambiance.

227
00:13:27,850 --> 00:13:29,650
Wait, let me pose.

228
00:13:35,150 --> 00:13:36,150
Let me look.

229
00:13:36,150 --> 00:13:37,610
This is blurry. We'll retake photos outside.

230
00:13:37,610 --> 00:13:39,456
The lighting is not good.

231
00:13:48,270 --> 00:13:50,850
Mom, I need to tell you something.

232
00:13:50,850 --> 00:13:53,010
I didn't want to tell you at first.

233
00:13:53,010 --> 00:13:56,800
It was a man's secret between me and Kai.

234
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:57,930
What is it?

235
00:13:57,930 --> 00:14:00,320
Remember my school fight last time?

236
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:02,470
How could I forget?

237
00:14:02,470 --> 00:14:05,952
They were talking trash about
you and Kai behind my back.

238
00:14:05,952 --> 00:14:08,690
Otherwise, I wouldn't have fought them.

239
00:14:10,150 --> 00:14:11,970
Why didn't you tell me then?

240
00:14:11,970 --> 00:14:15,610
I didn't want you to blame yourself.
Kai thought the same.

241
00:14:17,312 --> 00:14:19,810
Eat up before it gets cold.

242
00:14:19,810 --> 00:14:24,230
I never thought there was anything wrong
with you and Kai being together.

243
00:14:24,230 --> 00:14:25,890
Actually, I'm really happy

244
00:14:25,890 --> 00:14:29,450
because now, there's another person
to protect you with me.

245
00:14:31,584 --> 00:14:33,650
I understand now.

246
00:14:38,948 --> 00:14:41,056
 

247
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:47,010
Hey, Meng.

248
00:14:47,010 --> 00:14:48,890
 Where are you, sweetie? Busy this afternoon? 

249
00:14:48,890 --> 00:14:51,150
I'm having lunch with Jia Yu.

250
00:14:51,150 --> 00:14:54,050
It's fine. Mom, go with Godmother this afternoon.

251
00:14:54,050 --> 00:14:56,050
I'm meeting Wang Si Si at the library.

252
00:14:56,050 --> 00:14:57,088
Alright, I'm free now.

253
00:14:57,088 --> 00:14:58,270
Where are you?

254
00:14:58,270 --> 00:15:01,190
 - Let's meet at the cafe. 
- Okay.

255
00:15:10,340 --> 00:15:12,220
What's with the grumpy face?

256
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:14,080
Arguing with someone?

257
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:18,820
Li Jin Yu again? What's wrong now?

258
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:21,300
Now, he's learned to stand me up.

259
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:24,060
Last night, we agreed
to adopt a cat from a cattery.

260
00:15:24,060 --> 00:15:26,020
Now, he's pretending to be busy.

261
00:15:26,020 --> 00:15:28,600
He just doesn't want me to have a cat.

262
00:15:30,020 --> 00:15:33,600
Are you two fighting or flirting?

263
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,520
Just flirting.

264
00:15:36,388 --> 00:15:37,408
But I really feel...

265
00:15:37,408 --> 00:15:40,340
Do you think we've hit the marriage slump phase?

266
00:15:40,340 --> 00:15:43,760
You two? Impossible.

267
00:15:43,760 --> 00:15:46,680
You're practically glued together 24/7.

